peopleAlsoAsk.question: Are insulators worth any money?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Condition - The condition of the insulator can also greatly affect value. Naturally the more damage an insulator has, the lower its value. Insulator price guides generally give a range of values (e.g. $20-30). The high end value is usually Mint (no damage), and the low end value would be Near Mint (some damage).

peopleAlsoAsk.question: What are the rarest insulators?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Like bottles, aqua is the most common color, but some of the rarest insulators are aqua. A few insulators were factory-coated with carnival glass or a flashed amber. The most sought after colors are cobalt blue, yellow, 7-Up green, and purple.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: How can you tell how old an insulator is?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Look for a circle with an A in it. If it is followed by two numbers, the first number is the mold number and the second number is the year +1900 the insulator was made. For example, (A) 39 49 means the insulator was made in 1949 with mold #39.
